Architecture plan for issues #23-#28

Project shape
- Vite + React + TypeScript single-page landing site with Tailwind CSS.
- Page composition lives in `src/App.tsx`, with reusable layout primitives in
  `src/components/layout`, navigation in `src/components/NavBar.tsx`, CTAs in
  `src/components/ui/Button.tsx`, and page sections in `src/sections`.
- Shared landing-page copy, anchor ids, and content-facing types live in
  `src/config/content.ts`; environment-specific CTA wiring lives in
  `src/config/env.ts`.

Module structure and file organization
- Add `src/components/Footer.tsx` for issue #23. It should consume
  `landingContent.brandName`, existing nav items, CTA config, and new typed
  footer/social/link content from `src/config/content.ts`.
- Keep footer placement in `PageShell` or `App` explicit. Prefer `PageShell`
  accepting an optional `footer` prop if the footer is part of the global page
  frame; otherwise append `<Footer />` after `<FinalCTA />` in `App`.
- Keep section-level responsive fixes in their owning files:
  `Hero.tsx`, `HowItWorks.tsx`, `Features.tsx`, `WhyFounders.tsx`, `FAQ.tsx`,
  `FinalCTA.tsx`, plus `NavBar.tsx`, `Footer.tsx`, `Container.tsx`, and
  `Section.tsx` when the issue is cross-cutting.
- Add test assets for issue #27 under a conventional path such as
  `tests/e2e/smoke.spec.ts` or `src/__tests__` depending on the selected test
  runner. For browser smoke coverage, prefer Playwright with a Vite preview or
  dev server command.
- Add deployment documentation for issue #28 in `README.md` or a focused
  `DEPLOYMENT.md`, and keep static build output in ignored `dist/`.

Shared types
- Extend `src/config/content.ts` with footer-specific types such as
  `FooterLink`, `SocialLink`, and `FooterContent`.
- Reuse `NavItem`, `AnchorHref`, `CtaConfig`, and `SectionId` for footer links
  rather than duplicating anchor strings.
- If animation config is needed for issue #26, colocate small prop types with a
  reusable wrapper such as `src/components/motion/Reveal.tsx`; keep content
  types separate from animation implementation details.

Dependencies between issues
- #23 footer should happen first because it adds the final page region that
  responsive, accessibility, animation, test, and deployment work must cover.
- #24 responsive pass depends on all visible sections and the new footer being
  present. It should verify mobile, tablet, desktop, and wide desktop widths.
- #25 accessibility pass should follow the footer and responsive work so
  semantics, focus order, keyboard behavior, contrast, and reduced-motion
  behavior are checked against the final page structure.
- #26 scroll/hover animation polish should follow accessibility decisions and
  must respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- #27 end-to-end smoke test should cover the full integrated page after the
  footer and key visible behavior are stable.
- #28 production build and self-hosted deployment prep depends on the smoke test
  and should document `npm run build`, `npm run preview`, serving `dist/`, and
  required environment variables such as `VITE_CTA_URL`.

Key design decisions
- Keep the site lightweight: no router, no global state library, and no extra
  component framework unless an issue clearly needs one.
- Keep anchor navigation typed through `sectionIds` and `AnchorHref` so nav and
  footer links stay consistent with actual section ids.
- Use semantic landmarks: one header, main content, and footer; sections should
  remain labelled and navigable.
- Prefer native controls for FAQ and navigation interactions. Any animation
  library introduced for #26 should be small, tree-shakeable, and limited to
  presentational reveal/hover behavior.
- Preserve WCAG AA contrast and visible focus states while polishing visuals.
- Build verification should use the existing Node toolchain:
  `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, then a static preview/server check against
  `dist/`.
